# electronics / skidl

SKiDL describes electronic circuits as Python code. You define `Part`s, `Net`s, and their connections in a script, then call `generate_netlist()` to emit a KiCad-format S-expression netlist (the primary text deliverable), plus optional XML BOMs and SPICE simulation. Python-only, MIT licensed.

controls do
  electronics.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  electronics.kicad_version: { label: "KiCad version", type: "select", options: "KICAD5, KICAD6, KICAD7, KICAD8, KICAD9" }
  electronics.erc: { label: "Run ERC (electrical rules check)", type: "toggle" }
