end

## Required reading
- SKiDL official documentation — https://devbisme.github.io/skidl/ (official, MIT, devbisme / Dave Vandenbout)
- devbisme/skidl source + README + examples — https://github.com/devbisme/skidl (official, MIT, devbisme / Dave Vandenbout)

## Render
```bash
# install
python3 -m venv /tmp/skidlenv && /tmp/skidlenv/bin/pip install skidl
# KiCad symbol libs required for Part lookup; install + point KICAD_SYMBOL_DIR if unset
#   macOS: brew install --cask kicad
#   export KICAD_SYMBOL_DIR=/Applications/KiCad/KiCad.app/Contents/SharedSupport/symbols
# render: run the script — it calls generate_netlist(file_=...)
/tmp/skidlenv/bin/python src/circuit.py
```

## Failure modes
- `Part('Device','R')` raises a library-not-found error when `KICAD_SYMBOL_DIR` is unset — install KiCad and export the symbols dir first.
- There is no standalone `skidl` CLI binary; it is a library — always run it via `python your_script.py`.
- Wrong `tool=` KiCad version vs installed libs causes lookup/format mismatch — match `generate_netlist(tool=...)` to your installed KiCad.
- Output is a text netlist, not a visual schematic — import into KiCad eeschema/pcbnew to view graphically.
